Vice-President Prof Yemi Osinbajo (SAN), will tomorrow, commission the Niger Delta Power Holding Company (NDPHC) Limited’s new 2×60MVA, 132/33KV substations and associated 132KV transmission lines in Abeokuta, Ogun State. According to a press statement, the state governor, Prince Dapo Abiodun, will join the vice-president to commission the Otta/Papalanto/Abeokuta composite project that is made up of a new 2×60MVA, 132/33KV relief substation for Abeokuta; line bay extension works at Otta, Papalantoro and old Abeokuta 132/33KV substation. He will also commission a new 77.5KM, 132K double circuit line, replacing the old and worn-out single circuit lines between Otta, Papalantoro old Abeokuta right-up to the new Abeokuta substation. According to the Managing Director/Chief Executive Officer (CEO) of NDPHC, Mr Chiedu Ugbo, the new 2×60MVA, 132/33KV substations of Abeokuta, when fully on stream, would provide reliable power off-take via six 33KV distribution feeders to the state capital (Abeokuta) and its environs. He explained further that the 1×60MVA transformer at Otta will provide additional power supply via three 33KV feeders to Otta and its environs. Ugbo underscored the importance of the projects, saying they would impact positively on power supply to Abeokuta, Otta axis and environs. How NDPHC delivered 112 projects in 13yrs to raise electricity transmission NPDHC: Reforming power sector with 10 GenCos, 21,000 substations FG commissions 330kv electricity substation in Yobe Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin